Statements: To make decisions, we use statements

1- if else statement [is used to make single decision]
   if(condition)
   {
      Code here will execute only if condition is true
   }
   else
   {
      Code here will execute only if condition is false
   }

2- if else if statement [is used to make multiple decisions]
    if(condition1)
       {
          Code here will execute only if condition1 is true
       }
    else if(condition2)
       {
          Code here will execute only if condition2 is true
       }
    else if(condition3)
       {
          Code here will execute only if condition3 is true
       }
       .....
       ....
       ....
       else
       {
          Code here will execute only if condition is false
       }


     multiple if [never use this] ---> even if this gets correct condition, it will check other and
                                       can produce incorrect result
     if-else     [To check single condition] {fastest}
     if else if  [To check multiple conditions]